1. Evaluator self-contradiction (03 ┬ž4.2 Ôćĺ ┬ž4.3): rewritten. ┬ž4.2 says the evaluator's outputs are metrics and optional artifacts, returned via the submission payload; it does NOT write trial fields directly. ┬ž4.4 now says the orchestrator performs the trial writes atomically with the terminal state event. 'MUST NOT modify ... other than the trial fields the submission writes and the task it holds a claim on' is the new negative rule.

